title: For Sale:  (New) Steyr Arms SSG 04 .308 Winchester MFG # 60.020.3G
postcontent: CALL TO VERIFY IN STOCK STATUS BEFORE DRIVING TO STORE OR BUYING ONLINE>Steyr Arms SSG 04 .308 Winchester MFG # 60.020.3G Steyr Arms SSG 04 .308 Winchester MFG # 60.020.3G The Steyr SSG 04 is a manually operated bolt-action rifle that offers an excellent choice to the long-range shooter or tactical operator in law enforcement or security applications. Available in a choice of the widely used caliber sizes of .308 Winchester or 300 Winchester Magnum, this platform provides high-precision performance and proven reliability.The .308 Winchester magazine holds 10 rounds and is available in either a 23.6-inch Heavy Barrel version or a 20-inch heavy barrel compact version. Both options feature a muzzle brake as well as a durable synthetic stock with an adjustable length-of-pull-- via stackable buttplate inserts-- and an adjustable cheek piece.As in other Steyr high-performance bolt-action rifles, the SSG 04 is built on the Safe Bolt System (SBS) action with a unique 2+1 safety function that offers three settings operated by a wheel switch on the tang of the stock. The FIRE mode (safety off) is indicated by a red dot, and the first level of SAFE mode disables the firing mechanism while allowing the bolt to be cycled. The second SAFE position locks the bolt, at which point the bolt can be pushed down against the stock, locking the firing pin and firing mechanism out of firing position, allowing safe transportation with a round in the chamber. Simply pressing the safety's release tab and rolling it forward returns the bolt to either the SAFE or the FIRE position. The receiver is topped with a Picatinny rail for optics mounting.Another feature in the SSG 04 is the 2-stage magazine securing mechanism that uses a first stage to lock the magazine in but allows the bolt to be operated without feeding rounds in the magazine, thereby providing the user with the options of dry-firing or loading individual rounds by hand while maintaining a full magazine at the ready. title: For Sale/Trade:  1912-61 Austrian Steyr in .308
postcontent: This is a contract rifle made for the Chilean government by Waffenfabrik Steyr in 1912 using the Model 1898 Mauser action.These rifles never left Germany as the outbreak of WWI stopped all exports... These stayed. Warehoused until well after the war. Originally chambered in 7x57 Mauser , these fine rifles were converted in 1961 by NATO to the new 7.62x51 .This conversion was done by removing the old barrels and then threading the  chamber back to the correct length as they were fitted with unissued U.S Ordnance 1903A3 barrels. 22" barrel on this short rifle pattern.This is a complete numbers matching rifle including the stock. No repairs , splits or cracks... Solid and whole but not the prettiest piece of 104 year old walnut . Still , though , matching number and cartouche stamped. Original sling.I have  had the bolt handle turned and have had the receiver drilled and tapped for scopemounts. Unfortunately , the bases cover the beautiful  crest of the Chilean government on the receiver. Weaver bases. Kwiksite See-through  mounts.This rifle shoots beautifully. Very accurate. I was getting regular groups under 3" at 100yds using surplus M80 ball ammo from the 60's with the iron sights....With a good scope you can drive tacks with quality ammo... Death to coyotes with 147gr FMJ....I am the first person to own this rifle since it was uncrated,  still packed in cosmoline.I have put about 300 rounds of assorted .308 factory hunting loads and brass and steelcased ammo in .308 and 7.62x51NATO military surplus  through this rifle in the last three years with no issues. Headspace was checked at purchase by certified gunsmiths , original bolt/proper headspace.Bore is still like new.A great rifle to enjoy as is ... OR...Get a nice synthetic (fiberglass) stock , glass bed it and have a wonderful , lightweight custom medium rifle...I have $650 in this with the numbers matching rifle then drilling/tapping /bases/mounts/and bolt turning....and I will take a loss for $500 cash...  Or trades listed below...I am clearing out my collectible/militaria/historical rifles at the moment...please check out my other listings , thanks.

postcontent: CALL TO VERIFY IN STOCK STATUS BEFORE DRIVING TO STORE OR BUYING ONLINE>Steyr Arms SSG Carbon .308 Winchester 23.6" Barrel MFG # 60.533.3ctSteyr Arms SSG Carbon .308 Winchester 23.6" Barrel MFG # 60.533.3ctThe Steyr SSG Carbon is the newest addition to the SSG family, and this rifle takes high-performance long-range shooting into the future with a compound carbon-fiber stock that creates a benchmark of extreme strength and durability. Unlike conventional carbon-fiber stocks made from woven carbon fabric that often suffer from side-strike structural failures, the SSG Carbon's stock is made using the same "chipped-carbon" Sheet Molding Compound (SMC) construction used to create load-bearing structures in Formula 1 racecars and high-performance aircraft. The SSG Carbon's chipped-carbon flakes combine thermally with the binding agent to form the SMC fror a distinctive appearance to the stock, but like the spirals on the rifle's cold hammer-forged barrel, they aren't just there for looks. The carbon chips interlock with each other to create an unparalleled tension net that is superior to steel in every direction, yet weighing a fraction of either steel or aluminum.Due to the unique recoil absorption properties of its SMC technology, the SSG Carbon is surprisingly lightweight, and its recoil absorption is unmatched. Utilizing the same barreled action and muzzle brake as the famed SSG 08, the SSG Carbon utilizes a direct trigger, legendary for its crisp, clean and repeatable break. A detachable box magazine functions either as a constant-feed magazine or it can be placed in a second position that acts as a magazine cutoff to single-feed the rifle over the tip of a loaded magazine.The SSG Carbon is built on the Safe Bolt System (SBS) action with a unique 2+1 safety function that offers three settings operated by a wheel switch on the tang of the stock. The FIRE mode (safety off) is indicated by a red dot, and the first level of SAFE mode disables the firing mechanism while allowing the bolt to be cycled. The second SAFE position locks the bolt, at which point the bolt can be pushed down against the stock, locking the firing pin and firing mechanism out of firing position, allowing safe transportation with a round in the chamber. Simply pressing the safety's release tab and rolling it forward returns the bolt to either the SAFE or the FIRE position.The stock of the SSG Carbon has multiple mounting points for sling attachments. It also features an adjustable cheek piece, an adjustable butt plate, rubber-wrapped pistol grip, and an integrated finely adjustable rear-elevation pod.
